Added:
- 1 server: extra capacity for split tiers
- 2nd HAProxy: LB cluster (VRRP/keepalived) to remove SPOF
- Split roles: web (Nginx), app (runtime), DB (MySQL) on separate machines
  -> better isolation, targeted scaling, security boundaries

Result:
- Scale web or app tiers independently
- LB cluster improves availability
- DB tier optimized for storage & replication

Talking points (1–2 minutes):
keepalived provides VRRP VIP to avoid LB SPOF.
split tiers let you scale web/app independently and isolate DB resources.
Operational notes: use IaC, monitoring, blue/green deploys, DB automated failover.
Screenshot_URL: https://imgur.com/REPLACE_TASK3

DNS -> VIP (keepalived VRRP)
↓
┌──────────────┐ HAProxy A (MASTER)
│ HAProxy A │ <---> HAProxy B (BACKUP via keepalived)
└──────────────┘
↓ ↓
┌────────┐ ┌────────┐ (Web tier - dedicated)
│ Web 1 │ │ Web 2 │
└────────┘ └────────┘
↓ ↓
┌────────────────────┐ (App tier - dedicated)
│ App 1 | App 2 │
└────────────────────┘
↓
┌────────────────────┐ (DB tier - dedicated)
│ DB Primary | DB Rep │
└────────────────────┘